Gråsort tragt

Thin-fleshed, not specially large.
Grey-black to brown, and sometimes with edges almost yellow.
Trumpet shaped, with a hollow stipe, dark hymenium strongly decurrent.
Forms ecotmycorrhiza with Fagus.

Craterellus cinereus is also dark but the hymenium has more wrinkles and the edges of the cap (or due to the shape, the end of the stipe) are more twitched.
Both are edible but Craterellus cornucopioides is tastier.
